## Using the Component with Tailwind CSS

This component supports **Tailwind CSS**, a utility-first CSS framework that allows you to quickly build and style user interfaces. With Tailwind CSS, you can easily apply pre-defined classes to achieve various styles and layouts.

To use the component with Tailwind CSS, follow the example below:

```jsx
const content = (
  <button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">
    I am an example button
  </button>
);

return (
  <Widget
    src="igris.near/widget/TailwindWrapper"
    props={{
      children: content,
    }}
  />
);
```

In this example, a `<button>` element is defined with Tailwind CSS classes applied to it. The classes `bg-blue-500`, `hover:bg-blue-700`, `text-white`, `font-bold`, `py-2`, `px-4`, and `rounded` are used to style the button.

You can modify the classes to customize the appearance and behavior of the button. Refer to the Tailwind CSS documentation for a comprehensive list of available classes and their respective styles.

The component will render the button styled according to the Tailwind CSS classes applied.
